<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1868,2039]" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,533,1904,1931]" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">Report associated with sponges:</emphasis>
This species was reported among seagrass 
<taxonomicName box="[1017,1184,1904,1931]" class="Liliopsida" family="Cymodoceaceae" genus="Amphibolis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="8" pageNumber="109" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1017,1145,1904,1930]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">Amphibolis</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
and demosponge with epiflora and fauna from Esperance, Duke of Orleans Bay (
<bibRefCitation author="Bartsch, I." box="[851,1006,1940,1967]" pageId="8" pageNumber="109" pagination="375 - 397" refId="ref13751" refString="Bartsch, I. (2005) The rhombognathine fauna of Australia (Rhombognathinae: Halacaridae: Acari) with notes on the fauna of Esperance, Western Australia. In: Wells, F. E., Walker, D. I. &amp; Kendrick, G. A. (Eds.), The Marine Flora and Fauna of Esperance, Western Australia. Western Australian Museum, Perth, pp. 375 - 397." type="book chapter" year="2005">Bartsch 2005</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1868,2039]" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,260,1977,2003]" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">Remarks</emphasis>
: This species is often abundant amongst the epifauna on seagrass 
<taxonomicName box="[985,1152,1976,2003]" class="Liliopsida" family="Cymodoceaceae" genus="Amphibolis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="8" pageNumber="109" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[985,1113,1976,2002]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">Amphibolis</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
, but present also amongst scrub-like corallines covering rocks (
<bibRefCitation author="Bartsch, I." box="[613,768,2012,2039]" pageId="8" pageNumber="109" pagination="375 - 397" refId="ref13751" refString="Bartsch, I. (2005) The rhombognathine fauna of Australia (Rhombognathinae: Halacaridae: Acari) with notes on the fauna of Esperance, Western Australia. In: Wells, F. E., Walker, D. I. &amp; Kendrick, G. A. (Eds.), The Marine Flora and Fauna of Esperance, Western Australia. Western Australian Museum, Perth, pp. 375 - 397." type="book chapter" year="2005">Bartsch 2005</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
